  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Caleph</span> are flying Re=
ptiles,
  large creatures that can have up to a 15 meters wing span. The <span
  class=3DSpellE>Caleph</span> vary largely in size, colour and looks. The
  different variations in the species rarely inter breed though. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Caleph</span> have a very c=
aste society,
  the various castes defined by skin colour. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Because of their natural ability for flight the <span
  class=3DSpellE>Caleph</span> are used to dealing and navigating in a 3D s=
pace.
  They make extremely good pilots and in space combat they are unequalled in
  ability.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Their natural flight ability has allowed the <span
  class=3DSpellE>Caleph</span> to develop a different type of fighter bay, =
the
  All Dimension Fighter Bay, this allows them to hold and repair fighters m=
uch
  more efficiently.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>The <span
  class=3DSpellE>Caleph</span> have also developed their own fighter craft =
that
  are <span class=3DSpellE>unequaled</span> in <span class=3DSpellE>maneuve=
rability</span>.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Caleph</span> seek out hot plac=
es for
  their homes. They do not have habitats like most races might, they claim =
land
  as territory, this can be as a family or pack or sometimes as an individu=
al. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Caleph prefer Fighters / Torpedo Bombers combine=
d with
  Torpedoes on smaller designs, with a Balanced approach to Energy Research=
.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
